# I want to see the category that is mostly ordered 

plt.figure(figsize = (10,5))

category_counts = df['Category'].value_counts()
category_order = category_counts.index

sns.countplot(x='Category', data=df, order = category_order)
plt.xlabel("Category")
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.title('Categories mostly ordered')
plt.xticks(rotation=90) 
plt.show();

The highest category being ordered are mobiles and tablets, men and women fitness, appliances and 'other'. The least ordered are Soghiaat, Home and Living, Helath and Sport, computing, books, school and education

shapefile_path = 'path_to_shapefile/shapefile.shp'  # Replace with the path to your shapefile
us_states = gpd.read_file(shapefile_path)

# Merge the shapefile with the revenue data
us_states_revenue = us_states.merge(pd.DataFrame(data), left_on='STATE_NAME', right_on='State', how='left')

# Plot the map chart
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
us_states_revenue.plot(column='Revenue', cmap='YlGn', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True)
ax.set_title('Revenue Generated by States')
plt.show();
